solutions.content:
# Intuition
DP 

# Approach
Let `dp` be an array of size $(n+1) \times 4$. Let 
- `dp[i+1][0]` represents the number of subarrays that *ends at `nums[i]`* and with desired minimum and maximum attained. 
- `dp[i+1][1]` represents the number of subarrays that *ends at `nums[i]`* and with desired minimum attained (but not for maximum). 
- `dp[i+1][2]` represents the number of subarrays that *ends at `nums[i]`* and with desired maximum attained (but not for minimum). 
- `dp[i+1][3]` represents the number of subarrays that *ends at `nums[i]`* and with neither maximum nor minimum attained. 

The transitions are intuitive. We are counting the number of subarrays that ends with `nums[i]` so we must include this number. Then there are naturally four cases: `nums[i]` achieves the minK, achieves the maxK, achieves both, and achieves neither. Just consider the effect of adding `nums[i]` to all subarrays that end with `nums[i-1]`, and we will figure out the transitions. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(n)$$, and can be improved to be $O(1)$ since only `dp[i-1]` is used (and can add the result to `res` on the fly). Code attached at the end. 

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long countSubarrays(vector<int>& nums, int minK, int maxK) {

        vector<vector<long long>> dp(nums.size()+1, vector<long long>(4, 0));
        // dp[i][0] up to i, min = mink, max = maxk, end at nums[i]
        // dp[i][1] up to i, min = mink, max < maxk, end at nums[i]
        // dp[i][2] up to i, min > mink, max = maxk, end at nums[i]
        // dp[i][3] up to i, min > mink, max < maxk, end at nums[i]
        for (int i = 1; i <= nums.size(); i++)
        {
            int val = nums[i-1];
            if (minK <= val && val <= maxK)
            {
                if (val == minK && val == maxK)
                {
                    dp[i][0] = dp[i-1][0] + 1;
                    dp[i][1] = 0;
                    dp[i][2] = 0;
                    dp[i][3] = 0;
                } else if (val == minK && val < maxK)
                {
                    dp[i][0] = dp[i-1][0] + dp[i-1][2];
                    dp[i][1] = dp[i-1][1] + dp[i-1][3] + 1;
                    dp[i][2] = 0;
                    dp[i][3] = 0;
                } else if (val > minK && val == maxK)
                {
                    dp[i][0] = dp[i-1][0] + dp[i-1][1];
                    dp[i][1] = 0;
                    dp[i][2] = dp[i-1][2] + dp[i-1][3] + 1;
                    dp[i][3] = 0;
                } else if (val > minK && val < maxK)
                {
