WINDOW = SUBARRAY
Keep record of the most recet index of minK and maxK in current window as it is needed while counting subarrays.
**Variables:**
mini = most recent index where nums[index] = minK
maxi = most recent index where  nums[index] = maxK
cnt   = no. of fixed bound subarrays
i       = left corner of current window
j       = right corner of current window

**Example:**  nums = [2,3,1,1,0,5,7]  minK=1, maxK=5
in window i = 0, j = 5
mini = 3(index of most recent 1), maxi = 5(index of most recent 5)

fixed bound subarrays are [2,3,1,1,0,5], [3,1,1,0,5], [1,1,0,5], [1,0,5]
observe [1,0,5] remains same we just iterate incrementing left index as 2,3,1,1 i.e, from i to min(mini, maxi)
cnt = min(mini, maxi) - i + 1;

when i = 0, j = 6 : nums[j] = 7 > maxK 
this window is of no use, max no. in the window should be maxK for being fixed bound subarray 
SLIDE THE WINDOW : i = j+1 because keeping jth index in window is of no use

**If it helps, please UPVOTE : )**

```
class Solution {
public:
    long long countSubarrays(vector<int>& nums, int minK, int maxK) 
    {
        int  n = nums.size();
        long long cnt = 0, mini = -1, maxi = -1; 
        int i = 0, j = 0;                        //for iterating nums

        while(j < n)                             //can also use for loop for j
        {
            if(nums[j] < minK || nums[j] > maxK) //subarray of no use now, move window
            {
                mini = maxi = -1;                //set new mini and maxi of new window
                i = j+1;                         //slide the window
            }

            if (nums[j] == minK) mini = j;       //update the index of recently observed minK
			if (nums[j] == maxK) maxi = j;       //update the index of recently observed maxK

            cnt += max(0LL, min(mini, maxi) - i + 1);  //if 2nd part of max is -ve means we don't have minK and maxK in window now so max(0, -ve) = 0, no increment

            j++;                                 //keep increasing the window towards right
        }
		return cnt;
    }
};
```

