finished after the contest :(

basically every time we find a valid window, we count the available subarrays within this window with
```
count += Math.min(max, min) - i + 1;
```
where i is the start of current window, Math.min(max, min) is the last index where the subarray is still valid
e.g. current window 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8, min 6, max 8
start is 0, Math.min(min, max) is 6
valid subarrays are: 0-8, 1-8... 6-8, so 6 - 0 + 1 = 7 windows
```
class Solution {
    public long countSubarrays(int[] nums, int minK, int maxK) {
        long count = 0;
        int min = -1, max = -1, j = 0, i = 0;
        for (; j < nums.length; j++) {
            // out of bounds: restart
            if (nums[j] < minK || nums[j] > maxK) {
                min = -1;
                max = -1;
                i = j + 1;
                continue;
            }
            //update min/max pointer
            if (nums[j] == minK) min = j;
            if (nums[j] == maxK) max = j;

            // from the start (i) to last available window index (Math.min(max, min))
            if (max >= 0 && min >= 0) count += Math.min(max, min) - i + 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```

