# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We need to find all subarrays having minimum value as minK 
and maximum value as maxK.

Now
I will have indices of 4 types
1 -> value greater than maxK or less than minK
2 -> indices with value as minK
3 -> indices with value as maxK
4 -> other left indices

We will exclude the first type of indices from our domain of possible indices to include because they will either disrupt maximum element or minimum element.

so now the formula for answer(number of subarrays) **after excluding the 1st type of indices** will be

Total Subarrays(excluding 1st type of indices) - subarrays with either no index with maxK or no index with minK(again excluding 1st type)
because if there is no index left with both 2 and 3 type of indices not present then atleast one of the two conditions will not be satisfied

Now by **Inclusion Exclusion principle**
count(not maxK index | not minK index) = 
count(not maxK index) + count(not minK index) 
-count(not maxK index & not minK index)

# Approach
So we have to just find number of subarrays excluding some type indices.
We can make a function for that which takes a set of indices which should not be included and returns the subarrays.
We can make a set of indices which should not be included for every type which we require. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
#define ll long long
class Solution {
public:
    long long countSubarrays(vector<int>& nums, int minK, int maxK) {
        if(minK>maxK){return 0;}
        ll n = nums.size();

        auto subcnt = [](ll cnt)-> ll{
            return (cnt*(cnt+1))/2;
        };

        function <ll(set<ll>)> sub = [&](set <ll> excluded){
            ll prev(-1); // previously excluded index
            ll ans(0); 
            for(auto x:excluded){
                ans += subcnt(x-prev);
                prev = x;
            }
            ans += subcnt(n-prev);
            return ans;
        };

        set <ll> tot,sMin,sMax,sAll;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(minK>nums[i] || maxK<nums[i]){
                tot.insert(i); sMin.insert(i); sMax.insert(i); sAll.insert(i);
            }else if(nums[i]==minK){
                sMin.insert(i); sAll.insert(i);
            }else if(nums[i]==maxK){
                sMax.insert(i); sAll.insert(i);
            }
        }

        ll total = sub(tot), notMin = sub(sMin), notMax = sub(sMax), notAll = sub(sAll);
        if(minK==maxK){return (total-notAll);}
        ll ans = total - notMin - notMax + notAll;
        return ans;
    }
};
```

