**SOLUTION USING QUEUE**

1. **Take a queue**
2. **initialize** three variables `minElementPosition = -1` , `maxElementPosition = -1` & `res = 0`
	* *At any given point minElementPosition & maxElementPosition will tell us if our queue contains minK & max or not*
3. **Iterate** over the given nums array
	4. **If**` nums[i] >= minK OR nums[i] <= maxK` (*element is in given range/good element*) 
			1. **Add** element into the Queue
			2. **If**` nums[i] == minK` **Then** `minElementPosition = queue.size()`
			3. **If** `nums[i] == maxK` **Then** `maxElementPosition = queue.size()`
			4. **If** `minElementPosition != -1 && maxElementPosition != -1 `
			**Then** `res += min(minElementPosition,maxElementPosition)`
			*i.e min(minElementPosition,maxElementPosition) this many subarray we can make with the elements in our queue*
	5. **Else**
		1. Clear the Queue (*Delete all elements from queue*) 
		2. Reset` minElementPosition = -1 , maxElementPosition = -1 `
			(*means we dont have minK & maxK in our queue*)

**This visualization will give you clear understanding of above steps & intution behind it**
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/99431d24-b69e-48eb-b661-9a41c2a577ad_1667221522.5965605.jpeg)

**Java Code**
```
class Solution {
    public long countSubarrays(int[] nums, int minK, int maxK) {
        Queue<Integer> q = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int minElementIndex = -1;
        int maxElementIndex = -1;
        Long res= 0L;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            if(nums[i] >= minK || nums[i] <= maxK){
                q.add(nums[i]);
                if(nums[i] == minK) minElementIndex = q.size();
                if(nums[i] == maxK) maxElementIndex = q.size();
                if(minElementIndex != -1 && maxElementIndex!= -1){
                    res += Long.valueOf(Math.min(minElementIndex,maxElementIndex));
                } 

            }
            else{
                q.clear();
                minElementIndex = -1;
                maxElementIndex = -1;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

