Take the ranges of the subarrays that does not contain minK or maxK. 

Example: [1,3,5,2,7,5] , minK = 1, maxK = 5

The ranges will be [1,3,5,2] [5]


Another Example: [1,3,5,2,5] , minK = 1, maxK = 5

The ranges will be [1,3,5,2,5]


Another Example: [5,3,7,1,7,2,3,1,4,5,8,6], minK = 2, maxK = 7

The ranges will be [5,3,7] [7,2,3] [4,5] [6]


Then we have to check how much subarrays are possible in this range only. There can’t be a subarray outside this range, because some element will be there lesser than minK or greater than maxK in between this range and next range.

In this range, traverse through all values and find how subarrays will come.

There are 3 cases:

* current element equal to minK - find closest right index that corresponds to maxK. 

Lets say closest right index that corresponds to maxK be 10 and this range last element index be 23. Then 23-10+1=14 subarrays are possible with this current element


* current element equal to maxK - find closest right index that corresponds to minK. 


* current element is neither minK nor maxK. find closest right index that corresponds to maxK and  also find closest right index that corresponds to minK. Choose the farthest index and count the subarrays


