suppose we have an array [1, 5, 2, 3, 4, 1, 5] how many subarray has 1 and 5?

if we begin with index 0, end index and be 1, 2, 3, 4 ,5, 6;
if we begin with index 1, end index and be 5, 6
so we can draw a table like
```
1, 5, 2, 3, 4, 1, 5
b  e  e  e  e  e  e
   b           e  e
      b           e
         b        e
            b     e 
               b  e
```
the number of e is the answer (12 in this example)

how do we get count of e for each b efficiently is key of this problem

suppose you stand at index 0 and look right, you seek for closest index of 5. if you can find 5, for subarray end with index of that 5 to end of whole array are all satisfied.

more generally, you need find closest index of 1 and index of 5 from right side, choose the larger one (so it contains both 1 and 5). and you know how many subarrays satisfied

how do we do it? we scan whole array from right to left. when you meet 1 or 5, we update the index value

```
index  0, 1  2  3  4  5  6  7 
       1, 5, 2, 3, 4, 1, 5,
--
idx1                        7
idx5                        7
--
idx1                     7  7
idx5                     6  7
--
idx1                  5  7  7
idx5                  6  6  7
--
idx1         5  5  5  5  7  7
idx5         6  6  6  6  6  7
--
idx1      5  5  5  5  5  7  7
idx5      1  6  6  6  6  6  7
--
idx1   0  5  5  5  5  5  7  7
idx5   1  1  6  6  6  6  6  7
```
now, for each index i, the number of satisfied subarray starting with index i is `n - max(idx1, idx5)`

but back to this question, how about number greater than 5 and less than 1? the easiest way is that you consider them as a spliter of whole array, and you just need count each subarray splitting by these values and summarize each result;

my code still needs some small tweaks for more efficient, but it is good enough to pass contest.

```
class Solution {
public:
  long long countSubarrays(vector<int>& nums, int minK, int maxK) {
    vector<int> buf;
    int64_t res = 0;
    for (int i : nums) {
      if (i > maxK || i < minK) {
        res += h(buf, minK, maxK);
        buf.clear();
      } else {
        buf.push_back(i);
      }
    }
    res += h(buf, minK, maxK);
    return res;
  }

  int64_t h(const vector<int>& nums, int minK, int maxK) {
    int n = nums.size();
    vector<pair<int, int>> right(n + 1, make_pair(n, n));
    for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
      right[i].first = right[i + 1].first;
      right[i].second = right[i + 1].second;
      if (nums[i] == minK) right[i].first = i;
      if (nums[i] == maxK) right[i].second = i;
    }
    int64_t res = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
      res += n - max(right[i].first, right[i].second);
    }
    return res;
  }
};
```

