**low_b=-1**:It is Lower bound ,it act as pointer in our program initialises with -1 because right now it is not pointing to any subarray bascially it will point to the left most index of the current subarray where the minK > nums[i] or maxK <nums[i] condition happens.

**smin** :It store the index of minK   which has the  last occurence in the  nums array and in other word it simply returns the indices of the most recent occurrences of  minK in the current subarray

**smax** :It store the index of maxK   which has the  last occurence in the  nums array and in other word it simply returns the indices of the most recent occurrences of  maxK in the current subarray

After that we have to just the compute the no. of subarray can be formed by finding the min value between the both the smin and smax and subtract it from  lowerbound afterward we have to return the maximum value by comparing them to (0,min(smin,smax)-low_b). 
