# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We would find index of minK and maxK, for a given starting find total subarrays.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We will iterate through the array for fixed starting index, but if we find any **num > maxK** or **num < minK** then we would move the starting index.

If we get both minK and maxK for given starting point, we can calculate total subarrays.
```
totalSubArrays = (min(maximumIndex, minimumIndex) - startingIndex + 1)
```
This gives all possible subarrays containing thes points.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
