# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Instead of traversing to all subarrays, come up with an approach where we can find out what value is the current number is contributing to the answer.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We keep track of the last minPos and maxPos seen. Also, it is important to keep track of from which position are we starting our subarray.

Iterate the array:
1. If the cur item is not in min max range, skip it reseting the tracker variables.
2. Update minPos and maxPos.
3. If any of the minPos and maxPos are not available continue.
4. Now main part:

Case 1: If cur number is minK, we need to check where was the last
maxK, based on that calculate how many subarrays can be form.
eg. [1,5,7,2,3,1,5], suppose we are index 6, so minPos will be 5, so we can subarrays like [3,1,5], [2,3,1,5], ... This     way it is easy to calculate the total contribution by this value.

Case 2: If current is maxK, similar to above approach calculate

Case 3: If current is inbetween range, then we just need to calculate from the index of min or max which appears first.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public long countSubarrays(int[] nums, int minK, int maxK) {
        long ans = 0;

        int minPos = -1;
        int maxPos = -1;

        int startSubArrayFrom = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            int cur = nums[i];

            if (cur < minK || cur > maxK) {
                minPos = -1;
                maxPos = -1;
                startSubArrayFrom = i + 1;
                continue;
            }

            if (cur == minK) {
                minPos = i;
            }

            if (cur == maxK) {
                maxPos = i;
            }

            if (minPos == -1 || maxPos == -1) {
                continue;
            }

            if (cur == minK) {
                ans = ans + (maxPos + 1) - startSubArrayFrom;
            } else if (cur == maxK) {
                ans = ans + (minPos + 1) - startSubArrayFrom;
            } else {
                ans = ans + Math.min(minPos, maxPos) + 1 - startSubArrayFrom;
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
```

